    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any form of recess made in one member of wood, metal, stone, or another material, particularly when the recess is made in order to receive another member. Included are rabbets, which are channels or grooves cut along the edge or face of a member, or rectangular recesses made along a projecting angle to form a step or shoulder.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
